{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Preheat oven to 200°C. Set aside a baking tray (30 x 40 cm).","Place chives, parsley and dill into mixing bowl and chop <nobr>3 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr>. Transfer into a bowl and set aside.","Place onion and garlic into mixing bowl and chop <nobr>4 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add butter and cook <nobr>3 min\/100°C\/speed 1<\/nobr>. Allow to cool in mixing bowl for 5 minutes.","Add cream, cream cheese, salt, pepper, lemon juice, capers (optional) and reserved herbs and mix <nobr>5 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add fresh and smoked salmon and combine <nobr>10 sec\/\/speed 2.5<\/nobr>.","Transfer pastry onto a sheet of baking paper (approx. 30 x 50 cm), overlapping pastry sheets by 1 cm and press together to form one sheet. Cut pastry into a 25 x 40 cm rectangle, discarding excess pastry. With long edge closest to you, place salmon filling onto bottom half of long edge, leaving a 1 cm border. Brush edges of pastry with a little of the beaten egg yolk, then fold pastry over to cover filling. Using a fork, press edges together to seal.","Transfer baking paper with pastry onto baking tray. Using a sharp knife, score a few lines on top of pastry, then brush with remaining beaten egg yolk (see Tips). Bake for 25-30 minutes (200°C) or until golden brown. Serve warm."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["4 sprigs fresh chives","2 sprigs fresh flat-leaf parsley, leaves only","2 sprigs fresh dill, fronds only","30 g brown onion","1 garlic clove","20 g salted butter","50 g pouring (whipping) cream","250 g cream cheese,  softened","1 pinch salt","2 pinches ground black pepper","20 g lemon juice","1 tbsp capers, drained (optional)","2 fresh boneless, skinless salmon fillet (approx. 150 g each), cut into pieces (approx. 5 cm)","150 g smoked salmon, cut into pieces (approx. 3 cm)","2 sheets puff pastry","1 egg yolk, lightly beaten, for glazing"]}],"id":"r136624","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-BUDRBA134vo\/XZVRvhvEPSI\/AAAAAAAAdSg\/IlbM0Jnihlo9QJVm4QK1tyUGd72GenSSgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_vwapOSRAVSFSgoqm.png","title":"Salmon en croute","publishedAt":"2017-01-15T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"36.1 g","fat":"60.3 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"29.5 g","calories":"3378 kJ \/ 804 kcal"},"usefulItems":"baking tray (30 x 40 cm), bowl, baking paper, pastry brush, oven","hintsAndTricks":["If time allows, place pastry-wrapped salmon into the refrigerator for 30 minutes before baking to allow flavours to develop. You can also freeze the unbaked pastry-wrapped salmon. Use within 2 weeks. Defrost completely in refrigerator before baking (as per step 8)."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","50m","4 portions"]}